Package com.project.neo.Baby

Class BabyController

java.lang.Object
com.project.neo.Baby.BabyController
@CrossOrigin(origins="https://neo-patient-care.herokuapp.com/") @RestController @RequestMapping public class BabyController extends Object
This class contains all resources for the API layer. It communicates directly with frontend through the different http requests that are annotated at the top of each method representing RESTful endpoints.

  • Method Details

    • returnBaby

      @GetMapping public List<Baby> returnBaby()
      This method returns a list of all baby objects currently in the MongoDB database.
      Returns:
      List of all baby objects in the database.

    • addNewBaby

      @PostMapping(path="/addBaby") public void addNewBaby(@RequestBody Baby baby)
      This method allows the user to add new babies into the system. This URL will not be accessible from the frontend to control who is able to add new babies into the system. To add a baby, the user will send a POST request to this URL with the body specifying the fields of the baby to be added, such as id and previous data.
      Parameters:
      baby - Baby object to be added.

    • returnTimestamps

      @GetMapping(path="/{id}") public List<Object> returnTimestamps(@PathVariable("id") int id)
      This method will return all fields of the baby object specified by id in order to display all data, including graphing out the sweat and prick data under the "view glucose levels" function in frontend.
      Parameters:
      id - specifies which baby object to return from the database
      Returns:
      returns baby object as a list of lists - each sublist stores a different field where: 1. Sweat timestamps 2. Sweat values 3. Prick timestamps 4. Prick values 5. Note Timestamps 6. Notes

    • deleteBaby

      @DeleteMapping(path="/{id}/delete") public void deleteBaby(@PathVariable("id") int id)
      This method deletes a baby by id that is currently stored in the database.
      Parameters:
      id - Id of baby to be deleted.

    • addNewNote

      @PostMapping(path="/{id}/addNote") public void addNewNote(@RequestBody com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.ObjectNode objectNode, @PathVariable("id") int id)
      This method adds a note be stored in the baby object note hashmap.
      Parameters:
      objectNode - Stores the JSON request body sent from frontend in object node. In this case, it allows extraction of the values specified under "time_instant" and "note".
      id - Specifies which patient to edit.

    • addNewPrick

      @PostMapping(path="/{id}/addPrickData") public void addNewPrick(@RequestBody com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.ObjectNode objectNode, @PathVariable("id") int id)
      This method allows users to add a prick data at a specific time instant to a specific baby stored in the database.
      Parameters:
      objectNode - Stores the JSON request body sent from frontend in object node. In this case, it allows extraction of the values specified under "time_instant" and "prick_data".
      id - Id of baby to store prick data in.

    • addCalibration
